-- Rinehart in Talks to Sell $2 Billion Coal Stake, Financial Review Reports
-- B y   R o b e r t   F e n n e r
-- 2010-10-17T20:14:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-17/rinehart-in-talks-to-sell-2-billion-coal-stake-financial-review-reports.html
Gina Rinehart, Australia’s richest
woman, is in talks to sell a stake in her coal assets in
Queensland state in a deal that may be worth as much as A$2
billion ($2 billion), the Australian Financial Review
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
situation. Rinehart’s Hancock Coal has received several bids and
may complete a deal soon, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Fenner in Melbourne at 
